<subSubSection id="C351869B0226467E83CAB52581ABFF7F" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="538" pageId="14" pageNumber="537" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF4D5100226467E83CAB52581ABFF7F" blockId="14.[151,1436,1798,2041]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="538" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis id="B93F09020226467F83CAB52583A8F8C2" bold="true" box="[199,400,1834,1861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
The epandrial ventral processes are divergent (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F80A3B5248620F8C3" box="[942,1048,1834,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). The epandrial extensions are located below the surstyli and they present flattened shape at their end (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F809FB54081C1F8EF" box="[914,1017,1870,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). Each surstylus has 30 to 35 surstylar teeth, irregularly arranged throughout the internal region, plus 6 thinner primary teeth arranged in a row and a tuft of long surstylar bristles (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F82B9B5988023F837" box="[436,539,1942,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). The hypandrium is elongated and thin; the median gonocoxites converge at the end and have hypandrial bristles (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F8114B5B480BBF853" box="[537,643,1978,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus appears sickle-like (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F8713B5B486BEF853" box="[1054,1158,1978,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). The central axis of the aedeagus has a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950226467F805FB5D08189F87F" box="[850,945,2014,2041]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="537">Fig.13B</figureCitation>
). The aedeagal apex has a hook shape, with a bipartite and pointed termination (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950227467E8124B2998088FF37" box="[553,688,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Fig. 13B, C</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus presents a pair of large and long lateral postgonites (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950227467E83ADB2B5831DFF53" box="[160,293,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Fig. 13B, C</figureCitation>
), which are in continuity with the phallapodeme and extend along the entire length of the central axis. The pregonites are fused at the end and have no bristles (
<figureCitation id="1370C9950227467E8018B2D181BEFF7F" box="[789,902,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1001,1025]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,301,960]" captionTargetId="figure-74@15.[151,1436,298,962]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Scanning electron micrographs of D. emarginata male terminalia. (A) Ventral view of hypandrium (554 x magnification). (B). Dorsal view of aedeagus. Arrow heads = a cleft on the dorsal region covered with scales (727 x magnification). (C) Lateral view of aedeagus (398 x magnification). (D) Ventral and dorsal view of terminalia, without aedeagus. (491 x magnification). The imagens are from JD strain. Abbreviations in Table 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5649988/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="538">Figs. 13C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
